article.description: Bryce Aiken had 28 points as Harvard narrowly beat Yale 88-86 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Aiken scores 28 to carry Harvard over Yale 88-86
article.linkText: Aiken scores 28 to carry Harvard over Yale 88-86
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Bryce Aiken had 28 points as Harvard narrowly beat Yale 88-86 on Saturday night. Aiken hit 13 of 15 free throws. Kale Catchings had 16 points for Harvard (14-9, 7-3 Ivy League). Danilo Djuricic added 14 points. Christian Juzang had 10 points for the road team. Miye Oni had 21 points for the Bulldogs (18-5, 8-2), whose six-game win streak was snapped. Alex Copeland added 21 points. Blake Reynolds had 15 points. The Crimson improve to 2-0 against the Bulldogs on the season. Harvard defeated Yale 65-49 on Feb. 1. Harvard matches up against Penn at home on Friday. Yale takes on Cornell at home on Friday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com

videos.headline: Aiken hits buzzer-beater to lift Harvard
videos.description: After Yale's Alex Copeland hits a 3-pointer to tie the score, Bryce Aiken calls game with a jumper as time expires to propel the Crimson.
